  "response": "The chances of securing admission with a rank of 986 in the BHU UET (Banaras Hindu University Undergraduate Entrance Test) for BA Social Science can vary based on several factors such as the total number of seats available, reservation categories, and the overall performance of other candidates.\n\nTypically, BHU has a limited number of seats for each course, and admissions are competitive. A rank of 986 might be on the borderline or lower-end for general category admissions, but it could still be possible depending on this year's specific cut-off trends and seat availability.\n\nTo get a more precise understanding, you should check the previous year's cut-off ranks for the BA Social Science course at BHU. Additionally, keep an eye on any official announcements or updates from the university regarding this year's admission criteria and seat allocation.\n\nIf you belong to a reserved category (SC/ST/OBC/PwD), you might have a higher probability of getting admission with this rank compared to general category candidates.\n\nFor the most accurate and specific information, consider contacting BHU\u2019s admission office directly, or visit their official website for detailed cut-off ranks and admission guidelines.",
